    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "In 1951 Pine Camp was renamed Camp Drum after Lt. General Hugh A. Drum, and in 1974 it became Fort Drum when a permanent garrison arrived.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        4,
        5
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fort_Drum"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "The 10th Mountain Division, famed for mountain warfare, has called Fort Drum home since 1974.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        28
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fort_Drum"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "During 1935 the largest peacetime maneuvers in U.S. history were staged on Pine Plains, drawing national attention to the area.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        14
